data.title: Cardinal Alessandro Farnese Jr. (1520-1589) – Find...
data.meta_description: Clergy. He was born in Rome as the eldest son of Pier Luigi Farnese, Duke of Parma and Girolama Orsini. His paternal grandfather Paul III, who had recently become pope, created him a cardinal at the age of fourteen in December 1534.
